headline: CarMax Stock Sinks After Earnings. Tariffs Could Drive Used Car Prices Higher, CEO Says.
summary: Shares of  CarMax  sank Thursday after the used-car dealer reported fiscal-fourth-quarter earnings that missed expectations and management sounded the alarm about the looming impact of auto tariffs.  The tariff will expand to imported car parts starting May 3, making it more expensive to assemble vehicles in the United States.  “I think it will it will push some folks into looking at used cars, late model used cars, which is interesting because that’s what we’re seeing a lot of interest in right now,” CarMax CEO William Nash said Thursday.

headline: Used-car retailer CarMax misses fourth-quarter profit expectations
summary: Used-car retailer CarMax on Thursday reported a fourth-quarter profit that missed Wall Street estimates, as higher borrowing costs kept some consumers from making big ticket purchases. Shares of the Richmond, Virginia-based company fell 7.5% in premarket trading. Used-car retailers' sales have been under pressure from a post-pandemic trend of consumers gravitating towards new vehicles with improved features and better financing options.
